Instructions to build the DIALS documentation pages using sphinx

Assumptions:

i)  you have the dials htdocs repository checked out:
      svn+ssh://svn.code.sf.net/p/dials/htdocs/code/trunk
ii) you have sphinx and dependencies (docutils, etc.) installed in your
    cctbx.python.


1) Install biopython if you donâ€™t already have it (this is to populate the
   publications section):

$ curl http://biopython.org/DIST/biopython-1.65.tar.gz > biopython-1.65.tar.gz
$ tar -xzvf biopython-1.65.tar.gz
$ cd biopython-1.65
$ dials.python setup.py build install


[this step is only necessary if you want to use the alabaster theme]
2) Get the alabaster sphinx theme:

$ curl https://pypi.python.org/packages/source/a/alabaster/alabaster-0.6.3.tar.gz > alabaster-0.6.3.tar.gz
$ tar -xzvf alabaster-0.6.3.tar.gz
$ cd alabaster-0.6.3
$ dials.python setup.py build install


[this step is only necessary if you want to use the alabaster theme]
3) Then replace the current sphinx configuration with the one using the alabaster theme:

$ cd $(libtbx.find_in_repositories dials)/doc/sphinx
$ mv conf.py conf_default.py
$ ln -s conf_alabaster.py conf.py


4) Build the documentation using the dev.dials.make_sphinx_html command which
   builds the sphinx documentation and copies the output into the
   sources/htdocs/doc directory.

$ dev.dials.make_sphinx_html


5) View the documentation! e.g. on mac:

$ open $(libtbx.find_in_repositories htdocs)/doc/index.html
